    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-22T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-22T03:00:00-05:00" n="53"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d53">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="from"
                            >Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-22T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 22, 1932—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Department’s 18, January 20, 5 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Pursuant to <persName corresp="#p_MMGFR1">General McCoy</persName>’s
                        request I yesterday attended the meeting of the Manchurian Commission, one
                        session in the morning and a concluding session in the afternoon which
                        lasted until a late hour. The Commission will not meet again here and the
                        Commissioners have left Geneva.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>I orally apprised the Commission of <persName corresp="#p_MMGFR1">General
                            McCoy</persName>’s acceptance as a member and stated that I was formally
                        so informing the President of the Council.</item>
                    <pb facs="0149" n="45" xml:id="pg_45"/>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>As all of the members of the Commission voted for Lord <persName
                            corresp="#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName> as chairman I likewise acquiesced
                        in his designation, making it unanimous.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>I am preparing a telegram giving the chief points taken up in the meeting
                        and certain details concerning which it will be convenient for <persName
                            corresp="#p_MMGFR1">General McCoy</persName> to be informed.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GPB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
